# Final comments
- Best Model: Random Forest delivered the best performance for fraud detection.

- High Accuracy and Precision: Balanced precision and recall with minimal false positives.

- Feature Importance: Identified key factors contributing to fraud.

- Handling Imbalanced Data: Used class weighting and undersampling to address imbalanced classes.


# Recommedations
- Implement Real-Time Monitoring Systems to flag suspicious transactions immediately.

- Continuous Model Training to keep up with evolving fraud patterns.

- Advanced Anomaly Detection to catch unknown types of fraud.

- Improve Feature Engineering by adding context-specific indicators (e.g., location, behavior).

- Multi-Layered Security such as MFA and biometric verification for high-risk actions.

- Collaborate on Data Sharing to leverage fraud patterns from other companies.
